<TITLE> 10 hurt in bus blaze after collision </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Manikganj, Sept 19 (bdnews24.com)  At least 10 passengers were hurt as a bus caught fire after colliding with another bus in Shibaloy, Manikganj, on Saturday, police said. Shibaloy police chief Mohammad Moniruzzaman told bdnews24.com the bus passengers were injured scrambling to get down from the vehicle. He said incident occurred just before 2pm as a Sohel Paribahan bus, bound for Dhaka, lost control and ran into another bus head-on at Arpara on the Dhaka-Paturia highway. The first bus caught fire after its CNG cylinder burst following a collision, Moniruzzaman said. Firemen arrived at the spot and put out the fire, but the bus was gutted before they could put out the blaze. The burnt-out bus was impounded, the local police chief added. bdn
